segment.source: The Packages Results pane in the Application Virtualization Server Management Console displays a list of the available packages.
segment.target: The Packages Results pane in the Application Virtualization Server Management Console displays a list of the available packages.

segment.source: Right-click any package in the Results pane to display a pop-up menu that contains the following elements.
segment.target: Right-click any package in the Results pane to display a pop-up menu that contains the following elements.

segment.source: Add Version
segment.target: Add Version

segment.source: Starts the Add Package Version wizard.
segment.target: Starts the Add Package Version wizard.

segment.source: On the Add Package Version page, in Full path for package file, you can enter or browse to the correct path.
segment.target: On the Add Package Version page, in Full path for package file, you can enter or browse to the correct path.

segment.source: On the Enter Relative path for package file page, you can enter the relative path in the Relative path for package file field.
segment.target: On the Enter Relative path for package file page, you can enter the relative path in the Relative path for package file field.

segment.source: Displays the Properties dialog box for the selected package.
segment.target: Displays the Properties dialog box for the selected package.

segment.source: The Properties dialog box displays the GUID information, the package name, and a list of applications (including version number and enabled status) associated with the package.
segment.target: The Properties dialog box displays the GUID information, the package name, and a list of applications (including version number and enabled status) associated with the package.
